      "lesson title": "AI and Public Trust: Managing Transparency Expectations",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how errors made by artificial intelligence systems can affect the public's trust in the institutions that use them. You will learn why transparency matters when AI goes wrong, and how organisations can communicate openly with the people they serve. We will look at real-world examples of how poor handling of AI mistakes has damaged confidence in public bodies, businesses, and government services. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of what the public expects when AI is involved in decision-making, and why managing those expectations honestly is essential. No prior technical knowledge is required, making this an accessible starting point for anyone working in or around public-facing roles.",
