          "subtitle": "Steps to restore public confidence",
          "slidecontent": "• Acknowledge the error quickly and clearly, without jargon or deflection\n• Explain what went wrong in plain language\n• Outline the concrete steps being taken to fix the problem\n• Transparent action, not just words\n• Communicate progress updates regularly so the public can see change happening\n• Invite feedback and show it is genuinely being acted upon"
        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "slidetitle": "Key Points to Remember",
          "subtitle": "Core lessons for rebuilding public trust",
          "slidecontent": "• Acknowledge AI errors quickly and clearly, before public speculation fills the gap\n• Transparency rebuilds trust faster than silence\n• Plain language explanations matter more than technical accuracy for most audiences\n• Institutions that own their mistakes are seen as more credible, not less\n• Small, consistent actions (regular updates, open reporting) build confidence over time\n• A practical next step: review your organisation's current AI error response process and identify one gap to address this month"
